{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"80edf0d9-5c68-4b8e-83aa-2e0a3603004c","content":"I can help you analyze a .NET crash dump! None of my specialized skills cover dump *analysis* (only collection), but I can guide you through it directly.\n\nThe main tools for analyzing `.dmp` files are:\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze`** — cross-platform, .NET-focused (recommended)\n2. **WinDbg** — Windows, full-featured\n3. **lldb + SOS** — Linux/macOS\n\n**To get started, could you tell me:**\n\n- Is the `.dmp` file accessible in this environment (can you share the path)?\n- What platform are you on (Windows/Linux/macOS)?\n- Do you have `dotnet-dump` installed? (install via `dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump`)\n\nIf you'd like, I can run `dotnet-dump analyze <your-file.dmp>` here and inspect the exception, managed threads, and call stacks to find the root cause.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ff7d262a-1b16-4132-b1f1-34dd8b735474","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET app and wants to analyze it to find the root cause of the crash. Let me look at the available skills to see if any of them are relevant.\n\nLooking at the available skills:\n- `dump-collect` - This is for **collecting** crash dumps, NOT analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n- `dotnet-trace-collect` - This is for capturing diagnostic artifacts, not analyzing dumps.\n- `android-tombstone-symbolication` - For Android tombstone files, not .dmp files.\n\n\n- `apple-crash-symbolication` - For Apple .ips crash logs, not .dmp files.\n\nNone of the available skills are designed for analyzing .dmp files. Since the `dump-collect` skill explicitly excludes dump analysis, I'll need to help the user directly. For .NET crash dumps, the standard tools are `dotnet-dump analyze` for cross-platform support, WinDbg on Windows, or lldb with SOS on Linux/macOS. Let me ask if they have the dump file available and guide them through the analysis process.","outputTokens":536,"requestId":"C3C6:19A777:1C733D8:200FA9A:6A07C3AD"},"id":"dd9ef40f-1ac2-450e-92dc-5c227cf9c02a","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:09:14.118Z","parentId":"1a5fda35-a08e-4be8-bf61-ddb9ecaf4d3a"}
